<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and
        Camshaft - Clean, Inspect, and Measure - Crankshaft and Main Bearings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Crankshaft and Main Bearings</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect crankshaft gear for chips or excessive wear. Replace gear if required.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean each main bearing and cap in solvent and dry with filtered compressed air. Do not
                scrape gum or varnish deposits from main bearings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean internal oil passages of the crankshaft using a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">Stiff Nylon Brush</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001603"/>. Flush oil passages with a suitable non-caustic solvent.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Blow crankshaft oil passages dry with filtered compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect crankshaft journals (main and rod) for scratches, grooves, and scoring. Use
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">dye penetrant kit</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001603"/>
                to check for cracks.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect all upper and lower main bearings. Replace bearings that are scored, chipped, or
                excessively worn.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350016515" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk06/K06024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft journal measurement</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure diameter of each crankshaft journal at two points 90 degrees from each other using
                an
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">outside micrometer</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001603"/>. Move the micrometer over the entire width of the journal at each measurement
                point.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compare measurements to crankshaft
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_426.xml" xrefid="t335001601">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001601"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If crankshaft journals exceed maximum out-of-round or other specifications the crankshaft must be
                    reground or replaced.
                </para>
                <para>The crankshaft can be ground to the following undersizes:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>0.25 mm (0.010 in)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>0.51 mm (0.020 in)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>0.76 mm (0.030 in)</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
